The US Embassy in Nigeria has called on its citizens to review their personal security measures. The alert issued at the official site of the US Embassy Nigeria yesterday stressed that although the US has no specific threat information, it is prudent for the US Government to remind its citizens personal security actions to follow on a regular basis. The alert reads in part: ‘’Due to recent world events, US citizens should review their personal security measures. While we have no specific threat information, it is prudent to remind ourselves of the following personal security actions to follow on a regular basis. It called on its citizens to stay alert in public places, including schools, hospitals, government facilities, places of worship, tourist locations, and transportation hubs. The US Embassy Nigeria also called on its citizen to review and alter travel routes and times to reduce time and place predictability Other actions to take according to the Embassy are: ‘’Be aware of your surroundings; Keep a low profile; Avoid crowds and demonstrations; Exercise caution when walking or driving at night; Carry proper ID; Review your personal security plans; Monitor local media for updates.’’ 